<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3294/17.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-23"><hi rend="italic">February 23,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>French Government has submitted papers in case Jacobs as a matter of
                            courtesy; they seem regular to me and to counsel of embassy. Please see
                            my numbers 227 and 234 and cable instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McCormick.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>